commentary: Hamid Hassan to Gardiner, OUT full, straight, Gardiner plays all around it and sees the finger raised. Afghanistan are rewarded for keeping to a good plan in helpful conditions and credit to them for staying patient for the batsman to commit an error. Shouldn't have looked to play across the line to a ball that was not darting around. Pinned him in front of the stumps and he has to walk back. Albeit not without a long discussion about DRS. Think he made the right call not to go for it

commentary: Mohammad Nabi to Berrington, no run oof, did that touch anything? Nabi tossed it up and managed to defeat the batsman with his slowness and the hint of turn as well. Berrington has looked to push the ball down the ground, but the ball past the inside edge, and deflects off both pads and lands in between the top flap of the keeper's pad and his knee. The review was for caught behind, but there is no spike on snicko. Then we move to HawkEye, which says it pitched in line, impact was in line, but the ball hitting stumps was umpire's call. Looked a lot closer than that  on the lbw

commentary: Shapoor Zadran to Davey, OUT Hamid doesn't need to be bowling to pull off an outrageous celebration! Raced in from mid-off, dives forward and picks up a lovely catch to dismiss Davey. Poor shot - a drive on the up to a fuller delivery outside off - especially considering Afghanistan had brought Shapoor back for the express purpose of wickets. And the celebration - Hamid spreads his hands wide with just as wide a smile and tries to roll back and over his head. Doesn't quite succeed though

commentary: Shapoor Zadran to Haq, OUT clears his front leg and throws his all at a fuller ball outside off. He's held himself back to try and get Scotland to this point, but with only six balls remaining this was the way to go. Only he gets a thick edge that goes high towards point. Naib is down there, has to contend with a swirler and does it well as he dives to his left to hold on to a great catch

commentary: Wardlaw to Nawroz Mangal, 1 run dives, gets his fingertips to it, but it doens't stick! Magnificent effort from Mommsen, the captain, at second slip. This was back of a length and only a shade outside off, Mangal was trying to slide it away to third man but is surprised by the bounce and a hint of movement back at him. commentary: Evans to Nawroz Mangal, 3 runs now that's what I call a double team. Coetzer delivers the diving slide first,  but the ball was still headed to the boundary, so MacLeod who was backing up had to cut in and pull off a second diving save. What teamwork from Scotland. They're in this all the way, and finally Coetzer sends in the throw and in all the maniacal fielding, I forgot where the ball went

commentary: Davey to Gulbadin Naib, OUT Haq's on fire and Naib's been bounced out! commentary: Berrington to Dawlat Zadran, OUT but this will help Scotland! A rush of blood from Dawlat as he sizes up a length ball and throws his bat at it. Spies his bat as soon as it made contact, realising that he had not timed it at all. Mommsen runs back from short cover, takes a great catch staring up into the stun and tumbles over. Fielding to the fore again! And Shenwari bangs his bat into the turf at the non-strikers' end and stares daggers at Dawlat as he walks past him

commentary: Haq to Samiullah Shinwari, OUT length ball on middle and Shenwari has picked out deep midwicket! Haq goes mad, Shenwari is on his knees in despair! What an innings! What a performance! What passion! And spare a thought for Davey on the boundary, who kept calm and pouched a good, pressure catch. But wait... the third umpire is asking him to wait. He's checking if Scotland have adhered to the field restrictions. You're allowed four outside the circle. How many did Scotland have? They had the right people and Shenwari has to walk and he does so while counting the men on the deep in his mind

commentary: Wardlaw to Shapoor Zadran, FOUR runs he's done it! Shapoor has the vicroty and races off to one corner of the ground in his trademark celebration. The Scots are heartbroken, Shenwari is delirously happy! He wanted a yorker, ends up with a low full toss on leg stump and it's been picked off. Shapoor had stopped running as soon as the ball beat the short fine leg fielder. Spread his hands out wide and fell onto the turn in joy! What a match! What a performance! What theatre! This is how good the World Cup can be! This is how good it should be!
